item.Title: 1Br/1Ba in a Beautiful Edwardian Manor in Alameda Gold Coast
Description: Open House: Sunday 12pm-2pm

This 1Br/1Ba apartment is on the ground floor of a beautiful turn-of-the-century Edwardian Manor with all the architectural details, grand foyers and stairwells indicative of the style. This apartment gets plenty of sunlight all day, has lots of ample closet space, a separate living room, bathroom with claw-foot tub and hardwood floors.

The manor is located on the edge of the Gold Coast, just across the road from the Tree-and-Victorian-lined streets which make this beautiful residential enclave so famous. It is also located 1 block away from Franklin Park, a 15-20 minute walk to Park Street shops, restaurants and bars, and around the corner from buses ahead towards BART and throughout the Island.

item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special
Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.

This 1Br/1Ba apartment is on the ground floor of a beautiful turn-of-the-century Edwardian Manor with all the architectural details, grand foyers and stairwells indicative of the style. This apartment gets plenty of sunlight all day, has lots of ample closet space, a separate living room, bathroom with claw-foot tub and hardwood floors.

The manor is located on the edge of the Gold Coast, just across the road from the Tree-and-Victorian-lined streets which make this beautiful residential enclave so famous. It is also located 1 block away from Franklin Park, a 15-20 minute walk to Park Street shops, restaurants and bars, and around the corner from buses ahead towards BART and throughout the Island.

Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)

item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special
Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.

item.Title: Vintage Italian Steel - Marcello Faggin (Fah-Zheen) Special
Description: A gorgeous, classic Italian road bike by a legendary frame-builder.
A skillfully lugged and elegantly pantographed vintage Italian road bike. Paint is light metallic blue with yellow highlights and matching decals. No scratches, no dents.
I have received many, many compliments on this beautiful bike.
Frame: 54cm (center to center) Seat Tube and Top Tube (approx 21 inches)
Lightweight Columbus SL tubing throughout frame and forks.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.

The 6x2 drivetrain is the highly-sought-after Shimano 600 "Arabesque" with early Shimano Dura-Ace headset, brakes and hubs laced to 700c Mavic clincher rims. Cinelli stem and bars. Everything has been expertly cleaned, lubed, and tuned. The bike runs smoothly and efficiently.
ALL NEW: chain; cables and cable housing; bar tape; and Vittoria Open Corsa clincher tires w/ classic tan side-walls.

Retired bike racer Marcello Faggin started making bikes in Padua, Italy in 1945. He continued to hand-make steel frames through the mid-1980s. (This bike is estimated to be from the late-1970s, early-1980s.) Today, 70 years after the company was founded, it is still family-owned, and still focuses on quality steel bikes.

item.Title: 1Br/1Ba in a Beautiful Edwardian Manor in Alameda Gold Coast
Description: Open House: Sunday 12pm-2pm

This 1Br/1Ba apartment is on the ground floor of a beautiful turn-of-the-century Edwardian Manor with all the architectural details, grand foyers and stairwells indicative of the style. This apartment gets plenty of sunlight all day, has lots of ample closet space, a separate living room, bathroom with claw-foot tub and hardwood floors.

The manor is located on the edge of the Gold Coast, just across the road from the Tree-and-Victorian-lined streets which make this beautiful residential enclave so famous. It is also located 1 block away from Franklin Park, a 15-20 minute walk to Park Street shops, restaurants and bars, and around the corner from buses ahead towards BART and throughout the Island.

item.Title: OPEN TUESDAY 4:00-5:00 -- LARGE 1 BED - SLEEPS 3! 1/2 block to UC
Description: Open House Tuesday, 4:00-5:00 or call for appointment!
1815 Spruce is a wonderful, well-kept building, one half-block from campus. Surrounded by the Normandy Village apartments, it is two stories high with 14 large, light-filled apartments.
This apartment is a large 1-bedroom, approx. 800 sq. ft. There is ample room in the living area for couches and study space.
The bedroom easily fits up to 3 twin beds, with room for dressers, and a large closet.
The kitchen is in a separate room and features an eat-in dining area in front of a large window.
